-- Barclays May Take 100 Million-Pound PPI Charge, Times Says
-- B y   J e s s e   W e s t b r o o k
-- 2012-04-22T05:49:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/barclays-may-take-100-million-pound-ppi-charge-times-says.html
Barclays Plc (BARC)  plans to take an
additional charge of at least 100 million pounds ($161 million)
for improper sales of payment protection insurance, the Sunday
Times reported.  The bank plans to announce the provision to cover the costs
when it reports first-quarter financial results this week, the
newspaper reported without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
